issue,https://api.github.com/repos/eclipse-swtbot/org.eclipse.swtbot/issues/8,https://api.github.com/repos/eclipse-swtbot/org.eclipse.swtbot/issues/8,org.eclipse.swtbot,2352065194,8,LinkageError for org.hamcrest version,PatrickTasse,20052050,Patrick Tasse,,CLOSED,2024-06-13T21:05:04Z,2024-06-25T13:09:25Z,"When attempting to use the SWTBot 4.2.0 release for another project's CI, tests fail with a linkage error when it attempts to load different versions of org.hamcrest plugins. The platform uses version 2.2.0 while SWTBot uses version 1.3.0.

java.lang.LinkageError: loader constraint violation: loader org.eclipse.osgi.internal.loader.EquinoxClassLoader @68fc269b wants to load interface org.hamcrest.Matcher. A different interface with the same name was previously loaded by org.eclipse.osgi.internal.loader.EquinoxClassLoader @42312ee5. (org.hamcrest.Matcher is in unnamed module of loader org.eclipse.osgi.internal.loader.EquinoxClassLoader @42312ee5, parent loader 'platform')

During SWTBot 4.2.0 development, a restriction was added on the maximum version of org.hamcrest due to a breaking API change in version 2.1 (https://github.com/hamcrest/JavaHamcrest/blob/master/CHANGES.md#breaking-changes-for-21).

But if the use of the obsolete @Factory annotation is removed from SWTBot code, it can avoid the maximum version restriction and allow to use the same org.hamcrest version that is used by the platform.
